.DT
set_bottom_mess
Disk World creator help
set_bottom_mess

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
set_bottom_mess -  This function sets the position that non-living items will have when they are lying on the bottom in this room.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
void set_bottom_mess(string mess)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^mess%^RESET%^ - the new position for items lying on the bottom
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/room/basic/water.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This function sets the position that non-living items will have when they
are lying on the bottom in this room.  The default is "lying on the bottom".
.EP

.SH Example 1
.SI 5
  set_bottom_mess("lying in the seaweed");

.EI

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
query_bottom_mess
.EP

